article_title: Resistance to Taliban is doomed, says Russian envoy to Afghanistan
meta_description: Russia's ambassador to Afghanistan praised the conduct of the Taliban on Friday in the days since its takeover, saying there was no alternative to the hardline Islamist group and resistance to it would fail.  The comments by Ambassador Dmitry Zhirnov reflect efforts by Russia to deepen already well-established ties with the Taliban while stopping short, for now, of recognising them as the legitimate rulers of a country Moscow tried and failed to control before the Soviet Union withdrew its last forces in 1989.  Russia wants to ensure that the instability in Afghanistan does not spill over into Central Asia, part of the former Soviet Union it regards as its own backyard, and that the region does not become a launch pad for other extreme Islamist groups.

The moniker stands for Origins, Spectral Interpretation, Resource Identification, Security-Regolith Explorer, words which were supposed to explain the goal of the mission. Since they don’t, here it is in words we can all understand: a spacecraft tasked with taking a piece of an asteroid and bringing it back to Earth.

article_title: Asteroid 2016 AJ193 Travelling At 94,000 Km
meta_description: A massive asteroid bigger than than the world's tallest skyscraper Burj Khalifa will soar past Earth on August 21. Considered to be 'potentially hazardous', the asteroid is a cluster of 1,000 rocks. It has been named '2016 AJ193' by NASA.

article_title: What can we do with a captured asteroid?
meta_description: Asteroids are packed with gold and other valuable resources. And the best way to harvest those metals may be to bring space rocks to Earth.

article_title: 5 good reasons for the FDA to give full approval to COVID-19 vaccines: Analysis
meta_description: The FDA's approval might seem like a minor technical move to some.  All three vaccines currently have what's called "emergency use authorization" (EUA), which the FDA uses as a means to quickly give people access to potentially lifesaving medicines during a national crisis.  More than 358 million doses of COVID-19 vaccines have been safely administered in the U.S. -- and the incidence of complications as a result of the vaccines is minimal.

article_title: Forecasters offer grim fall outlook on COVID-19, with deaths predicted to rise in Mass.
meta_description: The dark coronavirus clouds that gathered over Massachusetts after July 4 brought a flood of new infections and rising hospitalizations that will continue into the fall, infectious disease experts agree. But the high-water mark, and how quickly the state turns that tide, depends on choices that can mean the difference between life and death.

article_title: Opinion: Booster shots alone will not save us
meta_description: Given this current landscape, a booster makes a lot of sense. What we must not do, however, is assume the third shot is the charm, writes Dr. Kent Sepkowitz. Rather, the booster is another temporary measure that will provide months of less worry.

article_title: Getting COVID-19 even when fully vaccinated, local health officials explain why
meta_description: More people are coming forward with "breakthrough" COVID-19 cases, meaning they're becoming infected even when fully vaccinated. This can happen when there's a high community spread of the virus, according to Dr. Elizabeth Dunmore, the Chief Medical Officer at Conemaugh Memorial Medical Center. "We are going to see breakthrough infections. That's going to happen. Of course, the more infections that we see from COVID-19, the more breakthrough infections we're going to see," she said.
